<paragraph blockId="8.[140,1108,1575,1672]" lastBlockId="9.[140,1108,167,264]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="258" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matheson" authorityYear="1912" box="[140,343,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Haliplidae" genus="Haliplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="257" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connexus">
<emphasis box="[140,343,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">Haliplus connexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common and widely distributed species in both 
<collectingRegion country="Canada" name="New Brunswick" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">New Brunswick</collectingRegion>
and on mainland 
<collectingRegion box="[417,560,1610,1636]" country="Canada" name="Nova Scotia" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">Nova Scotia</collectingRegion>
(Fig. 2). It was recorded from both provinces by 
<bibRefCitation author="Roughley RE" box="[175,374,1645,1671]" pageId="8" pageNumber="257" pagination="60 - 61" refId="ref6949" refString="Roughley RE (1991) Family Haliplidae: Crawling Water Beetles. In: Bousquet Y (Ed) Checklist of Beetles of Canada and Alaska. Ottawa, Ontario: Agriculture Canada, publication 1861 / E: 60 - 61. http: // www. canacoll. org / Coleo / Checklist / PDF files / HALIPLIDAE. pdf [accessed 5 January 2009]" type="journal article" year="1991">Roughley (1991)</bibRefCitation>
and from 
<collectingRegion box="[496,637,1645,1672]" country="Canada" name="Nova Scotia" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">Nova Scotia</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Matheson R" box="[680,884,1645,1671]" pageId="8" pageNumber="257" pagination="156 - 193" refId="ref6887" refString="Matheson R (1912) The Haliplidae of America north of Mexico. Journal of the New York Entomological Society 20: 156 - 193." type="journal article" year="1912">Matheson (1912)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Wallis JB" box="[941,1103,1645,1671]" pageId="8" pageNumber="257" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref7379" refString="Wallis JB (1933) Revision of the North American species (north of Mexico) of the genus Haliplus Latreille. Transactions of the Royal Canadian Institute 19 (1): 1 - 76." type="journal article" year="1933">Wallis (1933)</bibRefCitation>
. It has not been reported from Cape Breton Island. In Atlantic 
<collectingCountry box="[904,993,167,193]" name="Canada" pageId="9" pageNumber="258">Canada</collectingCountry>
there are records from small streams, eutrophic ponds, river margins, slow streams, and temporary ponds.
</paragraph>
